    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="505" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">1. f. 3r-38v: Maymar qālahu Yuḥannā ibn Zabadī ʻalá niyāḥat MartMaryam al-Sayyidah.-- 2. f. 42r-49r: Shahādat Anbā Qūris wa-Yūḥannā -- 3. f. 49v-52r: Qiṣṣat iẓhār ṣalīb rabbinā al-Masīḥ bi-Bayt al-Maqdis.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, lower gutter margin recto.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: Written in 15-17 long lines.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in New Style in black ink; pointed.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Rubrications in red.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: The date has been scrubbed, but probably mid-10th century. Copied by Thūmā, a monk of Saint Catherine's Monastary on Mount Sinai (f. 4r).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Binding: Bound in brown leather over wood with nails.</subfield>
    </datafield>
